description:
&lt;p&gt;Brighton &amp; Sussex University Hospitals NHS Trust Department of Anaesthetics is looking for enthusiastic individuals to work with us in our department to provide excellent, safe perioperative care to our patients. We are a keen teaching hospital, with lots of opportunities available to learn and develop your skills. Training and educational supervision will be provided to the level of the Kent, Surrey &amp; Sussex Post-Graduate Education and Assessment Regulations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will also be encouraged to take an active involvement in all departmental activities including audit and research, of which there are many opportunities available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts are based mainly in theatres and ITU at the Princess Royal Hospital site in Haywards Heath. Training will be provided, in the available subspecialties of anaesthesia. On call commitment will be a 1 in 7 or 1 in 8 rota, either covering the Obstetric unit or ITU and acute pain service rota. Daytime work includes training or solo lists, depending on departmental needs and competency of the individual.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details, please contact Dr Madhurima Das;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Madhurima.das1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NO AGENCIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Madhurima Das, Consultant Anaesthetist, BSUH&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: madhurima.das1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
